        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "RFC: Channel Echo / Session Pinning",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSession-level echo channels: pin a session to one or more delivery targets (Telegram thread, Discord channel, etc.) so every turn — both user input and AI response — echoes to all pinned channels regardless of which transport originated the turn.\n\n### Problem\n\nWhen a session is used across multiple transports (e.g. Telegram + AR glasses + web UI), each transport only sees messages sent/received through it. Telegram loses visibility of exchanges that happened on the glasses. The AI has full context (session history is the source of truth), but the human-facing chat logs are fragmented across transports.\n\n### Solution\n\n- Add `echoChannels: Array<{channel, to, threadId?, accountId?}>` to session entries\n- After primary delivery succeeds, fire best-effort copies to each pinned echo target\n- Echo both the user message and AI response so pinned channels have the complete conversation\n- Dedup: never echo back to the originating transport; `isEcho` flag prevents circular loops\n- All echo deliveries are fire-and-forget — never block primary delivery\n\n### User-facing API\n\n```bash\n# Pin a session to echo to a Telegram thread\nopenclaw sessions echo <sessionKey> --channel telegram --to 8661849123\n\n# Remove an echo pin\nopenclaw sessions echo <sessionKey> --remove telegram:8661849123\n\n# List echo pins\nopenclaw sessions echo <sessionKey> --list\n```\n\n### Implementation scope\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/config/sessions/types.ts` | `SessionEchoTarget` type + `echoChannels` field |\n| `src/config/sessions/store.ts` | Read/write `echoChannels` in session load/save |\n| `src/infra/outbound/echo.ts` (new) | Echo fanout: load targets, dedup, format, deliver |\n| `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts` | Post-delivery echo hook after `message:sent` |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods/chat.ts` | Echo user messages from webchat/gateway path |\n| `src/gateway/server-methods/sessions.ts` | `sessions.echo` method for add/remove/list |\n| `src/gateway/protocol/schema/sessions.ts` | Schema for echo target CRUD |\n\n### Motivation\n\nBuilt for the VituReClaw project (OpenClaw-native Viture Pro Neckband app) — when wearing AR glasses and talking to OpenClaw, the conversation should also appear in the Telegram thread you normally use, so you have a single persistent log regardless of which device you're on.\n\nSame pattern as IRC bouncers or Matrix bridging: session-level delivery fanout.\n\n## Status\n\nRFC only — design doc at `CHANNEL-ECHO-RFC.md`, no implementation code yet. ~11h estimated.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] Pin session to Telegram, send from glasses/webchat, verify echo appears in Telegram\n- [ ] Send from Telegram on pinned session, verify no double-echo back to Telegram\n- [ ] Pin to two targets, verify both receive echoes independently\n- [ ] Remove a pin, verify echoes stop\n- [ ] Verify primary delivery is never blocked by echo failures\n- [ ] Verify circular echo protection (`isEcho` flag)",
        "branch": "rfc/channel-echo",
